meMeanings":[{"name":"De","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Willington","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name from any or all of the places named  <i>Willington</i> (Beds, Cheshire, Derbys, Durham, Northumb, Warwicks), but there is little evidence from NE England."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Ralph","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Ralf","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."]}]},{"name":"III","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Japanese Yuko, Aiko, Hideaki, Hiroki, Hiroyuki, Isamu, Kaoru, Katsumi, Keiichiro, Kenji, Masako, Masayuki.","Japanese: variously written, sometimes with characters used phonetically; the most probable meanings are 仁井 ‘benevolent well’, 新居 ‘new residence’, or 新井 ‘new well’. It is not common in Japan."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ralph III De Willington was born about 1210, his father, Ralph de Wilington Constable of Bristol Castle, was 32 and his mother, Olimpia Chevaler, was 28. He married Joan Champernoun on 17 July 1238, in Sandhurst, Gloucestershire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died before 18 November 1256, in England, United Kingdom, and was buried in Umberleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1210–Bef 18 November 1256":"umbes 1210–enne 18. novembrit 1256","1210–1256":"1210–1256","1224–1309":"1224–1309","1239–1294":"1239–1294","1180–1242":"1180–1242","1184–1242":"1184–1242","Bef 18 November 1256":"enne 18. novembrit 1256","about 1193":"umbes 1193","1242":"1242","1184":"1184","1294":"1294","17 July 1238":"17. juuli 1238","1180":"1180","1239":"1239","about 1239":"umbes 1239","1224":"1224","1256":"1256","Abt 1210":"umbes 1210","Bef 1242":"enne 1242","1210":"1210","1 August 1242":"1. august 1242","1309":"1309","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Umberleigh, Devon, England":"Umberleigh, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sandhurst, Gloucestershire, England":"Sandhurst, Gloucestershire, England","Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1210–Bef 18 November 1256":"noin 1210–ennen vuotta 18. marraskuuta 1256","1210–1256":"1210–1256","1224–1309":"1224–1309","1239–1294":"1239–1294","1180–1242":"1180–1242","1184–1242":"1184–1242","Bef 18 November 1256":"ennen vuotta 18. marraskuuta 1256","about 1193":"noin 1193","1242":"1242","1184":"1184","1294":"1294","17 July 1238":"17. heinäkuuta 1238","1180":"1180","1239":"1239","about 1239":"noin 1239","1224":"1224","1256":"1256","Abt 1210":"noin 1210","Bef 1242":"ennen vuotta 1242","1210":"1210","1 August 1242":"1. elokuuta 1242","1309":"1309","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuning